                            <comment id="14017359" author="boday" created="Wed, 4 Jun 2014 04:27:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;why not just throw the exception if the expression is null AND maximumRequestsPerPeriod hasn&apos;t been set otherwise (by a previous message, etc).  That would prevent NULL expression evaluations for the first message and allow for subsequent ones, etc...      &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;something like this in Throttler calculateDelay()...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Throttler.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt; result = maxRequestsPerPeriodExpression.evaluate(exchange, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.class);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (result == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (maximumRequestsPerPeriod == 0 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; result == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RuntimeExchangeException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;The max requests per period expression was evaluated as &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + maxRequestsPerPeriodExpression, exchange);
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14110493" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2014 08:40:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ben do you have time to work on this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14110969" author="boday" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2014 17:19:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can, I was just waiting for some feedback...does that approach sound alright?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14111121" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2014 18:43:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ben, yeah this sounds like a good idea. I think you should try this change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
